eight={{Height|m=1.76}}\n|position=[[Forward (association football)|Forward]]\n|currentclub=\n|clubnumber=\n|youthyears1=1999\u20132001|youthclubs1=[[Kyoto Sanga FC|Kyoto Purple Sanga]]\n|years1=2002\u20132007|clubs1=[[Kyoto Sanga FC]]|caps1=18|goals1=2\n|years2=2007|clubs2=[[Tochigi SC]]|caps2=10|goals2=2\n|totalcaps=28|totalgoals=4\n|nationalyears1=|nationalteam1=|nationalcaps1=|nationalgoals1=\n|manageryears1=|managerclubs1=\n|medaltemplates=\n{{Medal|Team|[[Kyoto Sanga FC]]}}\n{{Medal|W|[[Emperor's Cup]]|[[2002 Emperor's Cup|2002]]}}\n}}\n\n{{Nihongo|'''Noboru Kohara'''|\u5c0f\u539f \u6607|Kohara Noboru|born July 22, 1983}} is a former [[Japan]]ese [[Association football|football]] player.\n\n==Playing career==\nKohara was born in [[Tondabayashi, Osaka|Tondabayashi]] on July 22, 1983. He joined [[J1 League]] club [[Kyoto Sanga FC|Kyoto Purple Sanga]] (later ''Kyoto Sanga FC'') from youth team in 2002. On October 12, he debuted as substitute forward against [[Urawa Reds]].<ref>{{J.League player}}</ref><ref>[https://data.j-league.or.jp/SFMS02/?match_card_id=6536 J.League]</ref> However he could only play this match until 2003. Sanga was also relegated to [[J2 League]] end of [[2003 J.League Division 1|2003 season]] and repeated promotion to J1 and relegation to J2 after that. Although he played several matches every season from 2004, he could not play many matches. In July 2007, he moved to [[Japan Football League]] club [[Tochigi SC]] and played many matches. He retired end of 2007 season.\n\n==Club statistics==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! colspan=3 | Club performance\n! colspan=2 | League\n! colspan=2 | Cup\n! colspan=2 | League Cup\n! colspan=2 | Total\n|-\n! Season !! Club !! League\n! Apps !! Goals\n! Apps !! Goals\n! Apps !! Goals\n! Apps !! Goals\n|-\n! colspan=3 | Japan\n! colspan=2 | League\n! colspan=2 | [[Emperor's Cup]]\n! colspan=2 | [[J.League Cup]]\n! colspan=2 | Total\n|-\n|[[2002 Kyoto Purple Sanga season|2002]]||row