{"title_page": "Pams (company)", "text_new": "{{for|the American jingle company|PAMS}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2015}}\n{{Use New Zealand English|date=August 2015}} uuuuussee\n{{Infobox company\n| name = Pams\n| logo = \n| caption = \n| type = [[Private label]]<ref name=\"private\">{{cite news|url=http://www.nzherald.co.nz/acnielsen/news/article.cfm?o_id=412&objectid=10358921&pnum=1|title=Private approach pays off|newspaper=[[The New Zealand Herald]]|first=Karen|last=Chan|date=8 December 2005|accessdate=29 January 2010}}</ref>\n| genre = \n| fate = \n| predecessor = \n| successor = \n| foundation = 1937; {{years ago|1937}} years ago\n| founder = \n| defunct = \n| location_city = \n| location_country = \n| location = [[New Zealand]]\n| locations = \n| area_served = [[New Zealand]]\n| key_people = \n| industry = [[Food]]\n| products = [[Groceries]]\n| production = \n| services = \n| revenue = \n| operating_income = \n| net_income = \n| aum = \n| assets = \n| equity = \n| owner = \n| num_employees = \n| parent = [[Foodstuffs]]\n| divisions = \n| subsid = \n| homepage = [http://www.pams.co.nz/ pams.co.nz]\n| footnotes = \n| intl = \n}}\n'''Pams''' (previously '''Pam's''') is a [[New Zealand]] [[company]], owned by [[Foodstuffs]],<ref name=\"private\"/> which also owns [[New World (supermarket)|New World]], [[Pak'n Save]] and [[Four Square supermarkets|Four Square]]. Pams sources and brands a wide range of supermarket goods as a [[house brand]].\n\n==History==\n[[File:Pam's.jpg|thumb|left|The old Pam's logo]]\nPams was formed in 1937 by [[Four Square (supermarket)|Four Square]].\n\n==Advertising==\nIn 2000 [[celebrity chef]] [[Jamie Oliver]] signed up on advertisements for Pam's, with the company also sponsoring Oliver's television show ''[[Oliver's Twist]]''.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nzherald.co.nz/business/news/article.cfm?c_id=3&objectid=2396989|title=Pam's happy to serve up big helpings of Oliver|newspaper=[[The New Zealand Herald]]|date=5 September 2002|accessdate=29 January 2010}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Portal|Companies}}\n* [http://www.pams.co.nz/ Official website]\n\n[[Category:Food and drink companies of New Zealand]]\n[[Category:Food and drink companies established in 1937]]\n[[Category:Store brands]]\n[[Category:New Zealand brands]]\n[[Category:1937 establishments in New Zealand]]\n\n\n{{NewZealand-company-stub}}\n{{food-company-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{for|the American jingle company|PAMS}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2015}}\n{{Use New Zealand English|date=August 2015}}\n{{Infobox company\n| name = Pams\n| logo = \n| caption = \n| type = [[Private label]]<ref name=\"private\">{{cite news|url=http://www.nzherald.co.nz/acnielsen/news/article.cfm?o_id=412&objectid=10358921&pnum=1|title=Private approach pays off|newspaper=[[The New Zealand Herald]]|first=Karen|last=Chan|date=8 December 2005|accessdate=29 January 2010}}</ref>\n| genre = \n| fate = \n| predecessor = \n| successor = \n| foundation = 1937; {{years ago|1937}} years ago\n| founder = \n| defunct = \n| location_city = \n| location_country = \n| location = [[New Zealand]]\n| locations = \n| area_served = [[New Zealand]]\n| key_people = \n| industry = [[Food]]\n| products = [[Groceries]]\n| production = \n| services = \n| revenue = \n| operating_income = \n| net_income = \n| aum = \n| assets = \n| equity = \n| owner = \n| num_employees = \n| parent = [[Foodstuffs]]\n| divisions = \n| subsid = \n| homepage = [http://www.pams.co.nz/ pams.co.nz]\n| footnotes = \n| intl = \n}}\n'''Pams''' (previously '''Pam's''') is a [[New Zealand]] [[company]], owned by [[Foodstuffs]],<ref name=\"private\"/> which also owns [[New World (supermarket)|New World]], [[Pak'n Save]] and [[Four Square supermarkets|Four Square]]. Pams sources and brands a wide range of supermarket goods as a [[house brand]].\n\n==History==\n[[File:Pam's.jpg|thumb|left|The old Pam's logo]]\nPams was formed in 1937 by [[Four Square (supermarket)|Four Square]].\n\n==Advertising==\nIn 2000 [[celebrity chef]] [[Jamie Oliver]] signed up on advertisements for Pam's, with the company also sponsoring Oliver's television show ''[[Oliver's Twist]]''.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nzherald.co.nz/business/news/article.cfm?c_id=3&objectid=2396989|title=Pam's happy to serve up big helpings of Oliver|newspaper=[[The New Zealand Herald]]|date=5 September 2002|accessdate=29 January 2010}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Portal|Companies}}\n* [http://www.pams.co.nz/ Official website]\n\n[[Category:Food and drink companies of New Zealand]]\n[[Category:Food and drink companies established in 1937]]\n[[Category:Store brands]]\n[[Category:New Zealand brands]]\n[[Category:1937 establishments in New Zealand]]\n\n\n{{NewZealand-company-stub}}\n{{food-company-stub}}\n", "name_user": "202.150.104.31", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pams_(company)"}
{"title_page": "2003 invasion of Iraq", "text_new": "{{short description|Military invasion led by the United States}}\n{{pp-move-indef}}\n{{redirects here|Invasion of Iraq|events after the invasion|Iraq War|the [[Mongol]] Invasion of Iraq|Siege of Baghdad (1258)|the British Invasion of Iraq during World War II|Anglo-Iraqi War|ongoing occupation of Iraq|Iraq conflict (2003\u2013present)|other invasions of Iraq throughout history|Military history of Iraq}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2019}}\n{{Infobox military conflict\n| campaign    = [[War on Terror|Global War on Terrorism]]\n| partof      = the [[Iraq War]]|<ref name=\"GlobalKansas\">{{cite news |title= President Discusses Global War on Terror at Kansas State University |publisher= White House |date= 23 January 2006 |url= https://georgewbush-whitehouse.archives.gov/news/releases/2006/01/20060123-4.html |accessdate= 29 October 2011 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20111028200751/http://georgewbush-whitehouse.archives.gov/news/releases/2006/01/20060123-4.html |archive-date= 28 October 2011 |url-status= live |df= dmy-all }}</ref>\n| image       = {{Photomontage\n   | photo1a = U.S. Marines with Iraqi POWs - March 21, 2003.jpg\n   | photo1b = Iraqi Sandstorm.jpg\n   | photo2a = US soldiers watch Iraqi paramilitary headquarter's burn Samawah, Iraq April 2003.jpg\n   | photo2b = Flag on Saddam Firdos Square Statues face 2003-04-09.jpg\n| position = center\n| size = 300\n| color = #F5F5F5\n| border = 2\n| color_border = black\n| spacing = 3\n| foot_montage =  \n}}\n| caption     = From left to right: Marines of the U.S. 1st Marine Regiment escort Iraqi prisoners of war; a convoy of U.S. military vehicles in a sandstorm; U.S. soldiers watch an enemy building in [[Samawah]] burn; Iraqi civilians cheer as a statue of Saddam Hussein is toppled.\n| date        = 20 March&nbsp;\u2013 1 May 2003<br />({{Age in years, months, weeks and days|month1= 3|day1= 20|year1= 2003|month2= 5|day2= 1|year2= 2003}})\n| place       = Iraq\n| casus       = The officially stated sole trigger for the invasion was the assertion by the U.S. and other allied governments that Iraq had failed comply with 17 successive [[United Nations Security Council|U.N. Security Council]] resolutions calling upon the country to disarm itself of [[Weapon of mass destruction|weapons of mass destruction]]; Iraq also expelled U.N. weapons inspectors from its country.\n| result      = Coalition operational success\n* <!--([[Saddam Hussein]]'s [[Arab Socialist Ba'ath Party \u2013 Iraq Region|Ba'ath Party]])-->[[Ba'athist Iraq|Iraqi Ba'athist]] government deposed\n* Occupation of Iraq [[History of Iraq (2003\u20132011)|until 2011]]<ref name=un>{{cite news|title= Security Council endorses formation of sovereign interim government in Iraq; welcomes end of occupation by 30 June, democratic elections by January 2005|url= https://www.un.org/News/Press/docs/2004/sc8117.doc.htm|publisher= United Nations|date= 8 June 2004|access-date= 5 June 2017|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20140923210327/http://www.un.org/News/Press/docs/2004/sc8117.doc.htm|archive-date= 23 September 2014|url-status= live|df= dmy-all}}</ref>\n* [[Al Maliki I Government|New Iraqi government]] established\n* Beginning of the [[Iraq War]]\n| combatant1  = '''Coalition forces:'''<br />\n{{flag|United States}}<br />\n{{flag|United Kingdom}}<br />\n{{flag|Australia}}<br />\n{{flag|Poland}}\n\n----\n''With military support from:''<br />\n[[Iraqi National Congress]]<ref>{{cite news |url= https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/articles/A42859-2003Apr6.html |title= U.S. Airlifts Iraqi Exile Force For Duties Near Nasiriyah |work= Washington Post |date= 7 April 2003 |accessdate= 13 September 2009 |first= Bradley |last= Graham |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20070808031321/http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/articles/A42859-2003Apr6.html |archive-date= 8 August 2007 |url-status= live |df= dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author= John Pike |url= http://