ish presidential election|President]]\n*17 May: [[Elections in the Dominican Republic|Dominican Republic]], [[2020 Dominican Republic general election|President<!-- (1st round)-->, Chamber of Deputies and Senate]]\n*20 May: \n**[[Elections in Burundi|Burundi]], [[2020 Burundian general election|President and National Assembly]]\n**[[Elections in Syria|Syria]], [[2020 Syrian parliamentary election|Parliament]]\n*25 May: [[Elections in Suriname|Suriname]], [[2020 Surinamese general election|Parliament]]\n\n===June===\n*17 June: ''[[Elections in Guernsey|Guernsey]], [[2020 Guernsey general election|Parliament]]''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-guernsey-50600187|title=New electoral roll launched for Guernsey elections|website=BBC}}</ref>\n*24 June: [[Elections in Mongolia|Mongolia]], [[2020 Mongolian legislative election|Parliament]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://montsame.mn/en/read/212133|title=Election day proposed to be on June 24|website=MONTSAME|date=9 January 2020}}</ref><!--\n*[[Elections in the Dominican Republic|Dominican Republic]], [[2020 Dominican Republic general election|President (2nd round)]]--><!--\n*[[Elections in Iceland|Iceland]], [[2020 Icelandic presidential election|President]] Election will be held only if an opposing candidate enters the race.-->\n\n===July===\n*2 July: [[Elections in Malawi|Malawi]], [[2020 Malawian presidential election|President<!-- (1st round) -->]]<ref>{{cite news |title=Malawi election re-run slated for July, says electoral commission |url=http://www.rfi.fr/en/africa/20200323-malawi-election-re-run-slated-for-july-says-electoral-commission |date=23 March 2020 |publisher=[[Radio France Internationale|RFI]] |accessdate=24 March 2020}}</ref><!--\n*[[Elections in Malawi|Malawi]], [[2020 Malawian presidential election|President (2nd round)]] -->\n\n===August===\n*30 August: [[Elections in Belarus|Belarus]], [[2020 Belarusian presidential election|President]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://belsat.eu/en/news/belarusian-presidential-election-2020-the-game-is-on|title=Belarusian Presidential Election 2020: The Game is On|website=Belsat TV}}</ref>\n*''[[Elections in the Falkland Islands|Falkland Islands]], [[2020 Falkland Islands electoral system referendum|Referendum]]''<ref>{{cite news |title=Falklands moves to next COVID-19 response; March 26 referendum postponed for six months |url=https://en.mercopress.com/2020/03/21/falklands-moves-to-next-covid-19-response-march-26-referendum-postponed-for-six-months |accessdate=26 March 2020 |work=MercoPress |date=21 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n===September===\n*6 September: ''[[Elections in New Caledonia|New Caledonia]], [[2020 New Caledonian independence referendum|Independence Referendum]]''\n*12 September: [[Elections in Iran|Iran]], [[2020 Iranian legislative election|Parliament (2nd round)]]{{citation needed|date=April 2020}}\n*19 September: [[Elections in New Zealand|New Zealand]], [[2020 New Zealand general election|Parliament]] and [[2020 New Zealand cannabis referendum|referendums on cannabis]] and [[2020 New Zealand euthanasia referendum|euthanasia]]\n*27 September: [[Elections in Switzerland|Switzerland]], [[2020 Swiss referendums|Referendum]]\n*''[[Elections in Hong Kong|Hong Kong]], [[2020 Hong Kong legislative election|Legislative Council]]''\n\n===October===\n*4 October: [[Elections in Kyrgyzstan|Kyrgyzstan]], [[2020 Kyrgyz parliamentary election|Parliament]]\n*11 October: \n**[[Elections in Lithuania|Lithuania]], [[2020 Lithuanian parliamentary election|Parliament (1st round)]]\n**''[[Elections in Northern Cyprus|Northern Cyprus]], [[2020 Northern Cyprus presidential election|President]]''\n*13 October: [[Elections in Liberia|Liberia]], [[2020 Liberian constitutional referendum|Constitutional Referendum]] and [[2020 Liberian senate election|Senate]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.indopremier.com/ipotnews/newsDetail.php?jdl=Liberia_sets_2020_referendum_on_presidential_terms&news_id=1450134&group_news=ALLNEWS&news_date=&tagi