{"title_page": "List of baseball parks in Toronto", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikimedia list article}}\n{{Cleanup|date=March 2009}}\nThis is a list of venues used for professional [[baseball]] in [[Toronto]], [[Ontario]]. The information is a compilation of the information contained in the references listed.\n\n;'''ballpark unknown'''\n:Occupant: Toronto - Ontario League (1884)\n\n;'''Jarvis Street Lacrosse Grounds'''\n:Occupant: Toronto - Canadian League (1885)\n:Location: Jarvis and Wellesley Streets (northwest corner) on William Cawthra's property; used from 1872 to 1890 for lacrosse by the Toronto Lacrosse Club and the Toronto Baseball Club 1885; sold with homes and church built on site; now residential and commercial district called Cawthra Square\n\n;[[Sunlight Park]] a.k.a. '''Toronto Baseball Grounds'''\n:Occupants:\n::Toronto Canucks [[International League|International League/Association]] 1886-1890\n::Toronto Canadians/Canucks/Royals/Maple Leafs [[International League|Eastern/International League]] (1895-1896)\n:Location: south-west of [[Queen Street East]] and Broadview, south to Eastern Avenue\n:Later usage: Converted to industrial, now some residential\n\n;[[Hanlan's Point Stadium]] a.k.a. '''Maple Leaf Park'''\n:Occupant: [[Toronto Maple Leafs (International League)|Toronto Maple Leafs]] - [[International League]] (1897-1900 or 1901 - sources vary) and (1908 or 1909 - sources vary - through 1925)\n:Location: Hanlan's Point on the [[Toronto Islands]]\n:Later usage: Converted to parkland after airport was built.\n\n;[[Diamond Park (Toronto)|Diamond Park]]\n:Occupant: [[Toronto Maple Leafs (International League)|Toronto Maple Leafs]] - [[International League]] (1901\u20131907,1909)\n:Location: Liberty Street and Fraser Avenue\n: Later usage: [[E. W. Gillett Company]] factory complex opened on site in 1912; now occupied by Kobo Inc.\n\n;ballpark name unknown\n:Occupant: Toronto Beavers - Canadian League 1914 (disbanded mid-season)\n:Location: unknown\n\n; [[Dominico Field]] (Christie Pits)\n: Occupant: Toronto Maple Leafs -Intercounty baseball (1969-present)\n: Location: Bloor Street West at Christie Street\n\n;[[Maple Leaf Stadium]]\n:Occupant: Toronto Maple Leafs - IL (1926-1967)\n:Location: the foot of [[Bathurst Street, Toronto|Bathurst Street]] on the south side of [[Lake Shore Boulevard]] (formerly Fleet Street); location also given as 555 Lake Shore Boulevard West, Stadium Road, Western Channel, Bathurst Street\n:Later usage: Public park and picnic grounds\n\n;[[Exhibition Stadium]]\n:Occupant: [[Toronto Blue Jays]] - [[American League]] (1977-1988)\n:Location: New Brunswick Way (right field); Lake Shore Boulevard (first base); Prince's Boulevard (left field)\n:Currently: site occupied by [[BMO Field]], 170 Prince's Boulevard\n\n;[[Rogers Centre]] orig. '''SkyDome'''\n:Occupant: [[Toronto Blue Jays]] - AL (1989-present)\n:Location: 1 Blue Jays Way (next to [[CN Tower]]), north of Lake Shore Boulevard, east of [[Spadina Avenue]].\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Baseball}}\n*[[List of baseball parks]]\n\n==Sources==\n*Peter Filichia, ''Professional Baseball Franchises'', Facts on File, 1993.\n*Michael Benson, ''Ballparks of North America'', McFarland, 1989.\n\n{{Baseball parks}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Baseball Parks, Toronto}}\n[[Category:Baseball venues in Ontario| Toronto]]\n[[Category:Lists of baseball venues|Toronto]]\n[[Category:Sports venues in Toronto]]\n[[Category:Baseball in Toronto|Parks]]\n[[Category:Toronto-related lists]]\n[[Category:Toronto Blue Jays|+]]\n[[Category:Ontario sport-related lists]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Wikimedia list article}}\n{{Cleanup|date=March 2009}}\nThis is a list of venues used for professional [[baseball]] in [[Toronto]], [[Ontario]]. The information is a compilation of the information contained in the references listed.\n\n;'''ballpark unknown'''\n:Occupant: Toronto - Ontario League (1884)\n\n;'''Jarvis Street Lacrosse Grounds'''\n:Occupant: Toronto - Canadian Le