{"title_page": "Shaghayegh Farahani", "text_new": "{{short description|Iranian actress|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2015}}\n{{more citations needed|date=February 2019}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name         = Shaghayegh Farahani\n| image        = Shaghayegh Farahani.jpg\n| imagesize    = \n| caption      =  \n| birth_date   = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1972|07|24}}\n| birth_place  = [[Tehran]], [[Iran]]\n| death_date   = \n| death_place  = \n| othername    = \n| yearsactive  = 1996\u2013present\n| occupation   = Actress\n| education    = [[Islamic Azad University|Azad University]] - Painting\n| spouse       = Divorced\n| website      = \n| parents      = [[Behzad Farahani]]<br>Fahimeh Rahiminia\n| relatives    = [[Golshifteh Farahani]] <small>(sister)</small> \n| notable role =\n| awards = \n}}\n'''Shaghayegh Farahani''' ({{lang-fa|\u0634\u0642\u0627\u06cc\u0642 \u0641\u0631\u0627\u0647\u0627\u0646\u06cc}}, born  24 July 1972) is an Iranian [[actress]]. She is the daughter of actor [[Behzad Farahani]] and sister of actress [[Golshifteh Farahani]].\n\n==Career==\n\nSome of her other works include \u2018Toutia\u2019 (1998), \u2018Cinderella\u2019 (2001), \u2018Butterfly in the Wind\u2019 (2003), \u2018Charlatan\u2019 (2004), \u2018The Trial\u2019 (2006),  \u2018The Story of Mozzafar\u2019 (2007), 'The Sinners' (2012), 'Metropol' (2013) and \u2018Resurrection Day\u2019 (\u2018Hussein Who Said No\u2019) (2014).\n\nShe has appeared in a few TV productions, including \u2018The Pahlavi Hat\u2019 (2012-2013), \u2018Matador\u2019 (2013), \u2018Motherly\u2019 (2013), \u2018A Beautiful Revolution\u2019 (2014).\n\n=== Personal life ===\nShaghayegh Farahani is the oldest daughter of veteran Iranian actor Behzad Farahani and stage actress Fahimeh Rahimnia.\nShe was married and some years later divorced. she became mother of a son named Sam at age of 20.\n\n===Selected filmography===\n* ''[[Leila (1996 film)|Leila]]'', 1996\n* ''Totia''\n* ''Love is not Enough'', 1998\n* ''[[The Pear Tree]]'', 1998\n* ''Nights of Tehran''\n* ''An Umbrella for Two'', 2001\n* ''Butterfly in the Wind'', 2004\n* ''Sharlatan'', 2005\n* ''[[The Guest (2006 film)|The Guest]]'', 2006\n* ''Jahan FC (film)|Bahareh in the Rain'', 2008\n* ''Metropol'' (2013)\n* ''[[Conditional release (film)|Conditional release]] '' 2016\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb name|0267044}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Farahani, Shaghayegh}}\n[[Category:Iranian actresses]]\n[[Category:Iranian film actresses]]\n[[Category:People from Tehran]]\n[[Category:1972 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Iranian women]]\n\n\n{{Iran-actor-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Iranian actress|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2015}}\n{{refimprove|date=February 2019}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name         = Shaghayegh Farahani\n| image        = Shaghayegh Farahani.jpg\n| imagesize    = \n| caption      =  \n| birth_date   = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1972|07|24}}\n| birth_place  = [[Tehran]], [[Iran]]\n| death_date   = \n| death_place  = \n| othername    = \n| yearsactive  = 1996\u2013present\n| occupation   = Actress\n| education    = [[Islamic Azad University|Azad University]] - Painting\n| spouse       = Divorced\n| website      = \n| parents      = [[Behzad Farahani]]<br>Fahimeh Rahiminia\n| relatives    = [[Golshifteh Farahani]] <small>(sister)</small> \n| notable role =\n| awards = \n}}\n'''Shaghayegh Farahani''' ({{lang-fa|\u0634\u0642\u0627\u06cc\u0642 \u0641\u0631\u0627\u0647\u0627\u0646\u06cc}}, born  24 July 1972) is an Iranian [[actress]]. She is the daughter of actor [[Behzad Farahani]] and sister of actress [[Golshifteh Farahani]].\n\n==Career==\n\nSome of her other works include \u2018Toutia\u2019 (1998), \u2018Cinderella\u2019 (2001), \u2018Butterfly in the Wind\u2019 (2003), \u2018Charlatan\u2019 (2004), \u2018The Trial\u2019 (2006),  \u2018The Story of Mozzafar\u2019 (2007), 'The Sinners' (2012), 'Metropol' (2013) and \u2018Resurrection Day\u2019 (\u2018Hussein Who Said No\u2019) (2014).\n\nShe has appeared in a few TV productions, including \u2018The Pahlavi Hat\u2019 (2012-2013), \u2018Matador\u2019 (2013), \u2018Motherly\u2019 (2013), \u2018A Beautiful Revolution\u2019 (2014).\n=== Personal Life ===\nShaghayegh Farahani is the oldest daughter of veteran Iranian actor Behzad Farahani and stage actress Fahimeh Rahimnia.\nShe was married and some years later divorced. she became mother of a son named Sam at age of 20.\n===Selected filmography===\n* ''[[Leila (1996 film)|Leila]]'', 1996\n* ''Totia''\n* ''Love is not Enough'', 1998\n* ''[[The Pear Tree]]'', 1998\n* ''Nights of Tehran''\n* ''An Umbrella for Two'', 2001\n* ''Butterfly in the Wind'', 2004\n* ''Sharlatan'', 2005\n* ''[[The Guest (film)|The Guest]]'', 2006\n* ''Jahan FC (film)|Bahareh in the Rain'', 2008\n* ''Metropol'' (2013)\n* ''[[Conditional release (film)|Conditional release]] '' 2016\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb name|0267044}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Farahani, Shaghayegh}}\n[[Category:Iranian actresses]]\n[[Category:Iranian film actresses]]\n[[Category:People from Tehran]]\n[[Category:1972 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Iranian women]]\n\n\n{{Iran-actor-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Bearcat", "label": "safe", "comment": "dabfix", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shaghayegh_Farahani"}
